## Enhanced Measurement Events {#enhanced-measurement}

GA4 tracks these automatically when enhanced measurement is enabled:

| Event | What It Tracks | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| page_view | Every page load and history change | Automatic, cannot disable |
| scroll | User scrolls past 90% of page depth | Single threshold only |
| outbound_click | Clicks to external domains | Captures link URL |
| site_search | Use of on-site search | Triggers on URL query parameters |
| video_engagement | YouTube embedded video interactions | Start, progress (10/25/50/75%), complete |
| file_download | Downloads of common file types | pdf, xlsx, docx, csv, etc. |

**Recommendation**: Leave all of these enabled. They provide a solid baseline with zero implementation effort. Supplement with custom events for business-specific actions.

