## Custom Events in GA4 {#custom-events}

### Using gtag.js (direct implementation)

```javascript
// Basic custom event
gtag('event', 'signup_completed', {
  'method': 'email',
  'plan': 'free'
});

// E-commerce purchase
gtag('event', 'purchase', {
  'transaction_id': 'T12345',
  'value': 99.99,
  'currency': 'USD',
  'items': [{
    'item_id': 'SKU_123',
    'item_name': 'Pro Plan Monthly',
    'price': 99.99,
    'quantity': 1
  }]
});

// CTA click with context
gtag('event', 'cta_clicked', {
  'button_text': 'Start Free Trial',
  'button_location': 'hero_section',
  'page_type': 'homepage'
});
```

### Using GTM Data Layer (recommended for most setups)

```javascript
// Push event to data layer
dataLayer.push({
  'event': 'signup_completed',
  'method': 'email',
  'plan': 'free'
});

// Push user properties
dataLayer.push({
  'event': 'user_login',
  'user_id': 'USR_12345',
  'user_type': 'premium',
  'account_created': '2024-03-15'
});

// E-commerce data layer push
dataLayer.push({
  'event': 'purchase',
  'ecommerce': {
    'transaction_id': 'T12345',
    'value': 99.99,
    'currency': 'USD',
    'items': [{
      'item_id': 'SKU_123',
      'item_name': 'Pro Plan Monthly',
      'price': 99.99,
      'quantity': 1
    }]
  }
});
```

### GA4 Recommended Events

Use Google's predefined event names when possible. These unlock enhanced reporting and integrations.

| Category | Events |
|---|---|
| Lead generation | generate_lead, sign_up, login |
| Content | search, select_content, share |
| E-commerce | view_item, add_to_cart, begin_checkout, purchase, refund |
| Engagement | page_view, scroll, video_start, video_complete |

Full list: https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/9267735

