## Custom Dimensions and Metrics {#custom-dimensions}

### When to create custom dimensions:

- You need to segment reports by a property not available by default (e.g., user_type, plan_tier, content_author)
- You want to filter or compare data using a business-specific attribute

### Setup steps:

1. Go to Admin > Custom definitions > Create custom dimension
2. Choose scope: Event (per-event value), User (persists across sessions), or Item (e-commerce)
3. Set the parameter name to match exactly what you send in the event

### Common custom dimensions:

| Name | Scope | Parameter | Use Case |
|---|---|---|---|
| user_type | User | user_type | Segment free vs paid behavior |
| plan_tier | User | plan_tier | Compare engagement by plan |
| content_group | Event | content_group | Group pages into categories |
| signup_method | Event | method | Understand registration sources |
| experiment_variant | Event | variant | A/B test analysis |

