## GTM Container Structure {#gtm-structure}

### Organizing your container

Use folders to group related items. A clean container is a maintainable container.

**Recommended folder structure:**
- GA4 Core (configuration tag + pageview)
- GA4 Events (all custom event tags)
- Conversion Pixels (Meta, LinkedIn, Google Ads)
- Utility (data layer variables, lookup tables)

### Naming conventions for GTM:

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Tags | [Type] - [Description] | GA4 Event - Signup Completed |
| Triggers | [Type] - [Description] | Click - CTA Hero Button |
| Variables | [Type] - [Name] | DLV - user_type |

### Best practices:

- Add version notes on every publish describing what changed
- Always use Preview Mode before publishing
- Use workspaces if multiple people edit the container
- Never hardcode values in tags when a variable or data layer value will work

