## Consent Mode v2 {#consent-mode}

### What it is

Google's Consent Mode lets you adjust how Google tags behave based on user consent. It is required for EU audiences if you use Google Ads remarketing or conversion tracking.

### Consent types

| Signal | Controls | Default (no consent) |
|---|---|---|
| ad_storage | Advertising cookies | denied |
| analytics_storage | Analytics cookies | denied |
| ad_user_data | Sending user data to Google for ads | denied |
| ad_personalization | Remarketing and personalization | denied |

### Implementation

```javascript
// Set default consent state (before GTM loads)
gtag('consent', 'default', {
  'ad_storage': 'denied',
  'analytics_storage': 'denied',
  'ad_user_data': 'denied',
  'ad_personalization': 'denied',
  'wait_for_update': 500
});

// Update when user grants consent
gtag('consent', 'update', {
  'ad_storage': 'granted',
  'analytics_storage': 'granted',
  'ad_user_data': 'granted',
  'ad_personalization': 'granted'
});
```

### With a CMP (recommended)

Most Consent Management Platforms (Cookiebot, OneTrust, Osano, etc.) have built-in GTM integrations that handle consent mode automatically. Configure through:
1. CMP dashboard: Set up consent categories
2. GTM: Use the CMP's community template tag
3. Test: Verify consent signals fire correctly in Preview Mode

