## Debugging GA4 and GTM {#debugging}

### GA4 DebugView

1. Enable debug mode by adding `?debug_mode=true` to any page URL
2. Or install the GA Debugger Chrome extension
3. Open GA4 > Admin > DebugView
4. Navigate your site and watch events appear in real time
5. Click any event to inspect its parameters

### GTM Preview Mode

1. Click "Preview" in your GTM workspace
2. Enter the URL of the page to test
3. A debug panel shows which tags fired, which triggers matched, and the data layer state
4. Make changes and re-test without publishing
5. Only publish after everything validates correctly

### Network Tab Inspection

1. Open Chrome DevTools > Network tab
2. Filter by `collect` (for GA4) or your analytics tool's endpoint
3. Inspect the payload to verify event names and parameter values
4. Check for duplicate requests (indicates duplicate tagging)

### Quick diagnostic checklist

- Is GTM loading? (check for `gtm.js` in Network tab)
- Is the data layer populating? (check `dataLayer` in Console)
- Is the trigger firing? (check GTM Preview Mode)
- Is the tag sending data? (check Network tab for collect requests)
- Is GA4 receiving it? (check DebugView or Realtime reports)
